# PacketcraftR 0.2.0

Source commit: `{{SOURCE_COMMIT}}`

Workspace archive SHA-256: `{{ARCHIVE_SHA256}}`

Post-publication downloaded-artifact smoke evidence: {{SMOKE_EVIDENCE}}

PacketcraftR 0.2.0 is the stable GitHub-only release of the runtime-neutral
packet kernel, bounded capture/replay and active-tool workflows, native
Linux/macOS/Windows adapters, and frozen v0.2 Rust/CLI/document contracts.

## Distribution

GitHub Releases are the only distribution channel. The attached
`packetcraftr-workspace-0.2.0.tar.gz` is the complete buildable workspace;
`SHA256SUMS` authenticates it. All five Cargo packages retain
`publish = false`; nothing is published to crates.io, docs.rs, or another
public registry. The MSRV is Rust 1.96.0.

Install the portable CLI from the verified extracted workspace with:

```console
cargo install --locked --path . --no-default-features
packetcraftr --version
```

## Frozen baselines

- Public Rust API: `319ac1647b8e40e9453178e418c40a26bfab98914df425b6e2c7dab1b8941762`
- CLI/schema: `{{CLI_SCHEMA_BASELINE}}`

## Qualified targets and limits

The approved release lineage passed portable and native checks on Linux x86_64,
macOS arm64/x86_64, and Windows x86_64 MSVC with Npcap 1.88, plus the shared
four-platform exact-byte and PCAP/PCAPNG interchange corpus. Native use still
requires the documented operating-system dependency and privilege boundary.

Darwin cannot transmit an exact caller-supplied IPv6 header through a raw IPv6
socket because the kernel synthesizes that header. PacketcraftR reports this as
typed `capability.unsupported` before I/O; exact IPv6 transmission on macOS is
qualified through native BPF Layer 2 instead of silently falling back.

See the [platform matrix](https://github.com/tyk-swe/pcr/blob/v0.2.0/docs/platform-support.md),
[installation guide](https://github.com/tyk-swe/pcr/blob/v0.2.0/docs/install-and-release.md),
and [migration guide](https://github.com/tyk-swe/pcr/blob/v0.2.0/docs/migration-v0.1-to-v0.2.md).
